Package de.tu_dresden.psy.efml

Interface Summary
AnyTag interface providing opening and closing operation for tags
 

Class Summary
AnswerCheckParser parses terms from <answer><check>-tags
AnswerCheckTokenizer turns a <answer><check>-term into a series of tokens
AnswerTag handles <answer>...</answer> tag, that can be used to create an answer button
BodyTag provides the body tag in the html file
CheckTag implements the <check>...</check> tag for answers
CorrectTag implements the <correct>...</correct> tag for answers
CTag implementation of the <c/> tag (switches column within <tables> tag)
DropdownTag implements the <dropdown>-tag for having a drop down box
EfmlTagsAttribute class that will store tag information when parsing EFML files
EfmlToHtmlConverter provides an interface that generates HTML files for the browser from EFML files
EfmlToHtmlHandler This class takes efml (xml) input from sax and generates intermediate structures that can be rendered to html.
HeadTag provides the head tag
HintTag implements the <hint>...</hint> tag for answers
HtmlTag implements the main html tag
IncludeAddendumTag implementation of the <includeaddendum/> tag (which is sort of hack & unsupported)
IncludeHoverTag implementation of the <includehover/> tag (which is sort of hack & unsupported)
IncludePreambleTag implementation of the <includepreamble/> tag (which is sort of hack & unsupported)
InstructionsTag implements class for <instructions> for adding an instructions button
LabelTag implements the <label>...</label> tag
OptionTag implements the <option>...</option> tag
PlainContent implements character data as child "tag"
RTag implementation of the <r/> tag (switches row within <tables> tag)
RunwayTag implements the <runway>-tag modelling an airfield that sends and takes "text" as planes via mouse interaction
SniffyTag implements class for <sniffy> for adding the sniffy button
StringEscape provides static functions that escape strings
TablesTag implements the <tables> tag, which puts a left-floating table around its contents
TagsTag implements the <tags>-tag, which can be used to propagate tags, atags and rtags attributes to child nodes without the need of another surrounding tag
TieTag implements the <tie> tag, which is for tie-together, i.e.
TitleTag  
UnknownTag this class represents an unknown tag which will just be reproduced as it was in the efml in the output html body
UnreadTag implements the <unread>...</unread> tag for instructions
UnusedTag implements the <unused>...</unused> tag for sniffy
WaitForTag implements the <waitfor>...</waitfor> tag for answers
